1. Data Loading

The load_data() function reads the CSV file using Pandas and displays:
	•	Total number of rows
	•	First few records of the dataset

This helps in understanding the structure of the data.

2. Data Cleaning

The clean_data() function ensures data quality by:
	•	Removing missing values
	•	Eliminating duplicate records
	•	Converting Price and Quantity into numeric format
	•	Dropping invalid numeric entries

3. Data Processing

The process_data() function:
	•	Creates a new column Revenue (Price × Quantity)
	•	Calculates total revenue
	•	Groups data by Category to find category-wise revenue
	•	Identifies top 5 products based on revenue

4. Data Analysis

The analyse() function:
	•	Converts the Date column into datetime format
	•	Groups data monthly to analyze sales trends
	•	Calculates average order value

5. Report Generation

The generate_report() function:
	•	Displays results in the console
	•	Shows:
	•	Total revenue
	•	Category-wise performance
	•	Top products
	•	Monthly trends
	•	Average order value
	•	Exports category-wise revenue into a CSV report file

6. Main Execution Flow

The program:
	1.	Checks if the CSV file exists
	2.	Loads the dataset
	3.	Cleans and processes the data
	4.	Performs analysis
	5.	Generates the final report
